description:
&lt;p&gt;Is being on the front line of the National Response to COVID something that interests you? Then why not join our team and help support us as we screen our staff and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Covid Lasham (Basingstoke) and Covid Mount (Winchester) units are part of the trust response to the Covid 19 pandemic. We operate a 7 day service from 07.30-19.00 providing pre procedure screening for patients as part of the trust restoration plan , and screening for our symptomatic staff and families to ensure a safe working environment for patients and staff at HHFT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition we operate a 7 day helpline service for staff where we provide guidance, clinical advice and support relating to Covid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IT skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathy to patients’ needs and concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to adapt to an evolving service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 12 month fixed term contract - Full /part time/Flexible hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All essential training will be given .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
